# Global EV Silicone Elastomer Market 2024-2030: Market, Size and Growth

The global electric vehicle silicone elastomer market has grown rapidly over the past few years due to the strong uptrend of electric vehicles and demand for high-performance materials that would render a vehicle safe, stronger, and energy-efficient. These silicone elastomers possess excellent thermal, chemical, and mechanical properties and are valued for their wide application areas in different electrical vehicle components such as battery seals, thermal insulation, gaskets, and cable insulation. This market is likely to grow significantly due to the increased shift towards electric mobility and stringent regulatory norms that focus on emissions. The demand for lightweight, yet extraordinarily durable materials, would form the major growth enablers in the automotive sector.

Key Growth Drivers
Increasing Electric Vehicle Adoption

The change in the global view toward low carbon content and fossil fuel usage has significantly enhanced demand for electric vehicles. The policies and regulations offered by governments around the world to promote the use of EVs add to the requirement for advanced materials like silicone elastomers, which are instrumental in enhancing component performance and lifespan in an EV.

Excellent Properties of Material
Silicone elastomers possess several advantages, for instance, high heat resistance, flexibility, electrical insulation, chemical stability, and toughness. These are factors that make them indispensable for the components of electric vehicles that are exposed to extreme environmental conditions such as high temperatures and electrical stresses. Silicone elastomers proved useful in sealing applications, gaskets, and even high voltage connectors.


